summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsSustainable PackagingGive BackFresh's Sugar Lip Balm Hydrating Treatments are 24 hour hydrating and powered by sugar from beet root and sugar cane that offers sheer, buildable color with a smooth, buttery texture.
details: DetailsBenefitsThe #1 Lip Treatment Brand in the U.S.*, Fresh offers a best-selling Sugar lip balm with 24hr hydration and sheer-to-buildable color that complements different skin tones for soft, smooth lips*Source: The NPD Group/U.S. Prestige Beauty Total Department/Specialty, Skincare Dollar Sales, Jan-May 2022Infused with sugar and plant-based fruit oils - including upcycled cranberry seed oil - this clear or tinted lip balm leaves lips feeling and looking healthy24hr proven hydration even as color wears**95% agreed it moisturized, softened & protected against dryness***12 buildable shades developed for a wide range of skin tones97% agreed lips looked and felt smoother*****instrumental test, 11 subjects***self-assessment, 62 subjects, 4 weeksKey IngredientsSugar is scientifically proven to have a long-lasting hydrating effectCranberry seed oil helps to smoothGrapeseed oil helps to softenVitamin C and E helps protectItem 2596652How To UseApply on lips as needed.IngredientsRicinus Communis (castor) Seed Oil, Simmondsia Chinensis (jojoba) Seed Oil, Cera Alba (beeswax), Vitis Vinifera (grape) Seed Oil, Helianthus Annuus (sunflower) Seed Wax, Hydroxystearic Acid, Parfum (fragrance), Oryza Sativa (rice) Bran Wax, Persea Gratissima (avocado) Oil, Limnanthes Alba (meadowfoam) Seed Oil, Sucrose Tetrastearate Triacetate, Vaccinium Macrocarpon (cranberry) Seed Oil, Citrus Limon (lemon) Peel Oil, Helianthus Annuus (sunflower) Seed Oil, Ribes Nigrum (black Currant) Seed Oil, Rosmarinus Officinalis (rosemary) Leaf Extract, Tocopherol, Ascorbyl Palmitate, Ascorbyl Tetraisopalmitate, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Ammonium Glycyrrhizate, Polyglyceryl-3 Polyricinoleate, Ethyl Vanillin, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-di-t-butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Propyl Gallate, Limonene, Citral, Linalool, Benzyl Alcohol, Geraniol, [may Contain: CI 77491, CI 77492 (iron Oxides), CI 15850 (red 7 Lake), CI 77891 (titanium Dioxide), CI 42090 (blue 1 Lake), CI 45410 (red 28 Lake)].Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Lip balm
reviews.comments: It always feels as comforting as lip balm with great color!

reviews.headline: Ugly 'berry' color:(
reviews.comments: The color of the packaging is so beautiful! Its like a WOW berry tone. Unfortunately the color of the product leaves much to be desired. It's like berry mixed with brown! I couldn't get past it. I didn't even want to try it on! I've wanted to try this product for years but just never got around to purchasing it. What a huge disappointment!

reviews.headline: They changed it
reviews.comments: Furst of all, let me say thus has been the ONLY lip product I gave used for at keast 15 years! I loved it! This used to be a wonderful creamy lip balm that left my lips moisturized and soft. Well, NOT ANYMORE! They have changed the formula or they are using inferior ingredients. This lip balm is dry and grainy! At first I thought I got a bad tube, so I bought a second one, still awfull! Both so dry and hard and NOT NOURISHING AT ALL! Waste of money! I'll be looking for a new go to!

reviews.headline: I will always buy this, please keep it available.
reviews.comments: Love this product. Product and packaging.

reviews.headline: Love The Moisture and Sheer, Buildable Coverage
reviews.comments: I hate matte lipsticks and lean toward natural, subtle colors to accentuate skin tone and eye color. I bought Aurora - a nice red with brown undertones and Petal - a nude/rose color. Aurora is great for a bold look, while Petal works well for a fresh look for any occasion.

reviews.headline: So good
reviews.comments: Made my lips soft and repaired cuts and stuff. Highly recommend

reviews.headline: Most expensive lip balm ever.
reviews.comments: Meh. I have to constantly reapply and its not very moisturizing for a balm. Esp at this price point.  Colors show very lightly but not really worth it.

reviews.headline: Not as hydrating as I'd hoped
reviews.comments: Has been eyeing this product for a while and finally splurged. A bit disappointed with the texture - it has more of a lipsticky feel than i was expexting. Doeant quite feel like a balm

reviews.headline: The Best
reviews.comments: While I can find the good in everything and with the variation of product ingredients; I believe you will never find another lip treatment that is better than this.  The smell is wonderful; the price is awesome and the results are second to none.  The color while not very obvious and not meant to be; is nice.

reviews.headline: Don't let the 5 star reviews influence you
reviews.comments: This product has great reviews, but I dont know how. I wanted this lip balm for a long and once I finally I was beyond disappointed. The color is nice, but very faint, especially on darker lips. However, this stuff will dry out your lips. Ive completely stopped using it after having to constantly reapply. Please save your money.

reviews.headline: Don't let the 5 star reviews influence you
reviews.comments: This product has great reviews, but I dont know how. I wanted this lip balm for a long and once I finally I was beyond disappointed. The color is nice, but very faint, especially on darker lips. However, this stuff will dry out your lips. Ive completely stopped using it after having to constantly reapply. Please save your money.

reviews.headline: For just a bit of tint
reviews.comments: I love this lip balm because I can apply it without a mirror and know that my lips will feel moisturized with a little color. It smells minty and looks cute in my purse.

reviews.headline: it is not worth this price in any way
reviews.comments: I hates this, I have the color rose. it is not pigmented enough for my medium/dark skin and is not hydrating. I really like tinted lip balms, and tinted chapstick and was really hoping this would live up to the hype. if you are looking for something more pigmented just get the Nivea ones there cheaper so are the CoverGirl ones to.

reviews.headline: Great color and sheen
reviews.comments: Ive been buying for 10 years and the besr thing sbout these is that you can apply with no mirror and its goong to look natural, give you a boost of color and sheen, and they taste great when they inevitably get in your mouth - not ariticial or weird. Hydrating and great for on the go.

reviews.headline: Love this product! Great moisturizer will colorðŸ©·
reviews.comments: Great moisturizer with alittle color!

reviews.headline: Color while wearing is not true
reviews.comments: It's definitely moisturizing, light, and feels great while wearing but the color has a very orange tint to it.  For the price I'm disappointed.

reviews.headline: Nope
reviews.comments: Reader, I need you to know im a lip balm addict. Name a brand w/ a balm, i own it. (I could be addicted to worse dont judge me). This one is garbage. I remember liking it years ago.. but theyve either changed the formula, or theres just too much on the marker thats better. Definitely pass on this one. Laneige, summer fridays, glossier, rhode even all have tinted balms that are LEAGUES better than this. < 3

reviews.headline: I didn't want to believe the bad reviews
reviews.comments: I used to love this stuff!  I ran out of an old tube and decided to repurchase...big mistake.  It feels very waxy and cheap.  Definitely not worth the price tag.  I decided it's not worth keeping even as a spare lip balm.  I don't want this on my body.  Looking for a new lip balm now.

reviews.headline: I will stop repurchasing since they changed the formula
reviews.comments: I have been repurchasing these for years, and now it definitely has a different formula.  The texture is not as creamy or emollient, and the color pay-off is gone.  It's no different than a run of the mill drugstore lip balm.

reviews.headline: A new favorite in my tool kit.
reviews.comments: Love the colors.

faceoff_positive.comments: I was SO glad that they finally got my ONLY lip color product back in stock! (Haven't worn lipstick in YEARS) I can tell it's a new formula. The old one was, at times, kind of mushy (especially if it got a little too warm), but the product had much more color deposit and felt more moisturizing than this version. This new formula is LESS 'mushy', but doesn't deposit as much color and doesn't last as long. While I wouldn't say that the previous formula was 'long lasting', the color had more of a stain-effect. This one, less so. So I find myself re-applying this one more often. Although I still love it more than regular lipstick, so I'll stand by it until I find something else I like!
faceoff_positive.headline: Different...undecided if it's as good

faceoff_negative.comments: I normally never write reviews, but this new formula is horrible. I have bought this product for years and didn't realize they changed their formula. My lips got dry and damaged and I didn't understand why as I applied my Sugar Lip Treatment on regularly. I actually thought I must have received a scam product but after looking up the reviews I realized it was due to the new formula. My lips was dry and damaged and I had to change to a brand new brand before it got better. Will never buy this again. So disappointed. Not recommended.
faceoff_negative.headline: New formula failure
